<p>Losing Louis, a play by <ref target="/wiki/Simon_Mendes_da_Costa" title="Simon Mendes da Costa">Simon Mendes da Costa</ref>, is a black comedy which first premiered at <ref target="/wiki/Hampstead_Theatre" title="Hampstead Theatre">Hampstead Theatre</ref> on 26 January 2005 and later transferred to <ref target="/wiki/Trafalgar_Studios" title="Trafalgar Studios">Trafalgar Studios</ref>. The original cast included <ref target="/wiki/Alison_Steadman" title="Alison Steadman">Alison Steadman</ref>, <ref target="/wiki/Lynda_Bellingham" title="Lynda Bellingham">Lynda Bellingham</ref> and <ref target="/wiki/Brian_Protheroe" title="Brian Protheroe">Brian Protheroe</ref>.</p>
<p>Secrets that refuse to remain buried erupt as family members are brought together, after years of segregation to face it all out in the bedroom - the place where all the confusion began. (Taken from the original promotion leaflet)</p>

